fields.prov_info: This copy of Marlowe's Faustus was bought at the sale of Henry Huntington on Thursday, April 25, 1918, by Mr. Speck. The book is number 313 of part VIII of the Huntington sale catalogue. It was a duplicate in the Huntington Library, and was probably sold because it was inlaid throughout, as so many of the Kemble books were. The sale catalogue says that the autograph notation on the title is in Kemble's hand. The book once belonged to the Duke of Devonshire.
